Background of the charity  
https://www.oyci.org.uk/parents-carers-supporters/#oyci  
Website: oyci.org.uk  
Founded: 2017, based on research into the lives of 10–18 year olds in   
Clackmannanshire  
Approach: Youth-led; children and young people lead the work  
Staff: 15 members  
Turnover: £300,000  
Mission: To ensure every young person in the area can flourish  
Vision: Universal youth work, with a focus on supporting more marginalised and   
vulnerable individuals as the charity grows  
Offerings: All services are free for users, including full school holiday programmes   
(with meals provided)  
Location: Clackmannanshire, Scotland; early policy tester for schooling schemes  
Growth Plan: Expanding reach to more marginalised and vulnerable young people  
Problem  
Young people and their families in Clackmannanshire face barriers to accessing OYCI’s   
services due to manual, fragmented, and sometimes exclusionary processes. Digital   
exclusion, complex booking systems, and a lack of integrated data make it harder for   
the most vulnerable to participate spontaneously or consistently.  
From the perspective of the organisation:  
- Key administrative processes (bookings, staff scheduling, data collection) are   
manual and time-consuming.  
- No central CRM; data is fragmented across platforms (Bookeo, Zoho People,   
Excel, MS365).  
- Bookeo’s booking system is restrictive (one account per email, which doesn’t   
reflect family structures).  
- Lack of integration between systems (e.g., staff leave in Zoho People doesn’t   
sync with Excel schedules or Xero payroll).  
- Manual processes create barriers to growth, limit capacity, and make it   
difficult to gather meaningful data.  
- The absence of streamlined systems prevents OYCI from scaling its impact   
and reaching more marginalised young people.  
Your impact  
How many people do you help in a year? approx 500 per year   
What impact will this project have on your organisation?   
- Significant time savings for staff and volunteers.  
- Ability to grow and support more young people, especially those currently   
excluded by digital barriers or administrative complexity.  
- Improved data collection and reporting to better understand and meet   
community needs.  
- Enhanced experience for young people and families, reducing barriers to   
participation.  
Current State  
Provide a summary of what happens now  
 What do you do currently?  
- Bookings are managed through Bookeo, but the system is restrictive and not   
family-friendly.  
- Staff scheduling is done manually in Excel, which is time-consuming and   
error-prone.  
- Staff leave is tracked in Zoho People, but this does not integrate with   
scheduling or payroll (Xero)  
- MS365 is used for general office productivity, but there is no centralised data   
or CRM.  
- Data collection is manual, making reporting and impact measurement   
difficult  
- No new digital solutions have been trialled due to limited capacity.  
 Has anything new already been tried internally? Not had the time to try anything   
due to capacity  
 Who are the stakeholders (people or teams affected)  
- Young people (primary beneficiaries)  
- Parents, carers, and families  
- OYCI staff (15 members)  
- Volunteers  
- Community partners
