- No CRM or central data repository  
Goal  
 What is the specific outcome you want to accomplish (from the perspective of the   
people you support) - Simple to use. Don’t want booking to be a barrier for entry   
but it helps the org actually shape what they do…   
- Implement a simple, user-friendly system for bookings and data   
management that does not exclude digitally disadvantaged families.  
- Ensure we can differentiate between number of bookings and number of   
young people accessing the service and how often e.g. 10 bookings could be   
3 young people accessing 3 or 4 times rather than 10 service users  
- Ensure the booking process is not a barrier, but a tool to help OYCI   
understand and respond to community needs  
- Integrate staff scheduling, leave management, and payroll to save time and   
reduce errors.  
- Enable spontaneous participation for individuals and families.  
- Address annual confidentiality renewals in a user-friendly way.  
- Reduce digital exclusion and make access as universal as possible.  
 Can you measure it?   
- Track reduction in admin time for staff.  
- Increase in number of spontaneous and repeat participants.  
- Improved data quality and reporting capabilities.  
- Feedback from families and young people on ease of use.  
 What is inside and outside of scope for this project?  
Inside:   
- Booking and data management system  
- Staff scheduling and integration with payroll  
- User experience improvements for families and staff  
Outside:   
- Broader organisational strategy  
- Non-digital aspects of service delivery  
 Any specific goals to help you achieve this outcome?  
- Remove barriers to participation for digitally excluded families.  
- Automate manual processes wherever possible.  
- Ensure all stakeholders (staff, volunteers, families) can use the system easily.  
 What is the reason for choosing this issue (versus others)?  
- Manual processes are the main barrier to growth and inclusion.  
- Addressing this will have the greatest impact on OYCI’s ability to reach more   
young people, especially the most marginalised.  
 Are all the stakeholders in agreement on your goal?  
All key stakeholders agree this is a priority as it is currently a barrier to growth.   
Is there a target timescale for the project?   
- As soon as possible; priority is on getting the right solution, but availability is   
good up until March next year.  
- Changemakers programme runs until November  
Barriers to Project  
 What constraints might prevent us from reaching the goal?  
- No budget ringfenced for digital solutions; most funding is allocated to staff.  
- Staff have limited digital skills and capacity for internal development.  
- Digital exclusion among some service users.
